    public interface JIPipeData
extends Closeable, AutoCloseable
    Base class for any JIPipe data wrapper class There must be a static function importData(JIPipeReadDataStorage, JIPipeProgressInfo) that imports the data from a row storage folder. Additionally, there must be an annotation of type JIPipeDataStorageDocumentation that describes the structure of a valid row storage folder for humans. The static importData(@link org.hkijena.jipipe.api.data.storage.JIPipeReadDataStorage}, JIPipeProgressInfo) method and the JIPipeDataStorageDocumentation annotation can be omitted for abstract data types or interfaces. JIPipeDataStorageDocumentation can be inherited from parent classes.

    Update: 1.74.0: The class is now closable, which is useful for handling external resources. JIPipeDataTable and JIPipeVirtualData were adapted to handle the close() automatically.
